                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On March 6 the Allied High Commissioners delivered to the Federal Chancellor, as
                    a reply to his assurance on debts, the text of the letter transmitted in <gloss
                        target="#t_Sigto1">Sigto</gloss> 464, February 22, page 1427, with the
                    following changes: (1) inclusion of the date “6 March, 1951” for the blank in
                    the first paragraph, (2) listing of the three governments in alphabetical order
                    in the first and last paragraphs, and (3) changing the last phrase of the second
                    sentence of the fourth paragraph to read “and interested Governments including
                    the Federal Government.” (762A.00/3–150)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
